Takeda Pharmaceutical Co. (4502)  may cut
jobs at a German unit,  Financial Times Deutschland  said, citing
comments by executive Frank Morich.  The cuts may happen at sites in Konstanz and Willinghusen,
 Germany , where a total of 600 people are employed, the newspaper
said.  The sites used to belong to  Altana AG (ALT) â€™s pharmaceutical
business, which was sold to Nycomed Holding AS, which has since
